&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to be Therapy Lead in the department of Speech, Voice and Swallowing at Wythenshawe Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a clinically strong, motivated and proactive clinician to join our team and assist in leadership of clinical areas including complex dysphagia, stroke, voice, community, ENT, and general inpatients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have significant and robust clinical experience and carry a caseload in one or more of these areas. In addition, the post holder will work with the Divisional SLT Lead to operationally lead and manage the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department has a strong reputation nationally and is at the forefront of developing SLT services in critical care and voice. We are involved in a range of research projects within these fields and actively encourage research and innovative practice.&lt;/p&gt;
